reviews.text: The experience was great! Everyone was so nice and the food was wonderful. Colette was an excellent server. We will definitely be back the next time we are in the area.

Always a go to for a healthy and farm to table breakfast when I’m in town. Great omelets, granola and other typical breakfast items. Haven’t had lunch there yet. Great interior design but I always opp for sitting outside. Easy location and around lots of great high end shopping after including a Starbucks across the street.
Brunch...same waiter we have had on weekends for 8 years...nice guy...great attitude. Great food.  Nice outside sitting area.

Tucked away in a small booth to escape the cold with my two-best friends. Food was savory and the service was thoughful and prompt. Nice place to spend a bit if time in a town that's always moving too fast for me.

Wonderful service, great location in Beverly Hills.   The Farm has more locals than tourists, it's that good.  If you're visiting this is an excellant place for breakfast lunch and brunch.  We live 8 blocks away and we frequently have breakfast, brunch there.

Worst buffet I've ever been too, all the meat was hard, wouldn't be surprised if it was sitting all day, selection was also really poor. Especially for the price! Don't waste your money or your time and don't chance your gut either STAY AWAY

The worst Chinese food I’ve had in ages. Had the vegetarian chop suey and it was just sprouts, 3 small pieces of celery, and 4 small pieces of carrots. Egg roll was awful. Spring rolls were disgusting. Avoid at all costs!

We didn’t eat their buffet but saw all the food sit there untouched for 45minutes. Def would avoid the buffet. 

Wow that was awful.
We always done take out. Always good good never had a bad experience.

I got food poisoning once there. The second time the waitress insulted my son. I will never darken their door again!
Go somewhere else!
We enjoyed the food and service! Was not used to Italian sausage in pasta sauce, not my taste. The rest of the food was very good and came out in a timely manner!
A really super experience. I hadn't been there in 20 years. A refreshing trip back to unique family-owned restaurants. Worth your time!

Luigi's is only open for lunch on Friday so we took advantage of the opportunity to change things up. Like a step back in time. An Augusta tradition for many years. A family owned restaurant similar to what you might have found in New York City or Chicago in the 40's.. Features wonderful fresh Greek and Italian cuisine. Great pizza. Greek style chicken and with a quarter you can play music from the music box right at your table. Lunch features either 1/2 order pasta dished or you can order from the full menu. The owner, Penny "Mama" Luigi was out front as usual but she left before we could speak to her. Tired of chain restaurants? Give Luigi's a shot. I promise you'll go back again.

Sorry to do this the a good staff, but the food was not good at all. The best thing was garlic bread.  We had to send back both of our meals.  We ordered chicken parm with Alfredo over pasta and the mashed potatoes with peppers. It was terrible!
Classic Italian/Greek restaurant if there was one. The service was amazing and very accommodating to my friend
